{{Infobox Architectural Practice |image = |caption = |name = Perry Dean Rogers |architects = Martha A. Pilgreen |city = [[Boston]] |coordinates= |founded = 1923 |dissolved = active |awards = |significant_buildings= |significant_projects = |significant_design = |}} '''Perry Dean Rogers''' is an [[architectural firm]] based in [[Boston]], [[Massachusetts]]. Founded in 1923 as Perry, Shaw & Hepburn, the firm became notable for its designs for educational institutions. The firm was responsible for the restoration of [[Colonial Williamsburg]]. The firm asserts their expertise in creating the [[Context (language use)|context]] of university environment. Perry Dean Rogers recently completed designing an entire college campus, masterplan and the individual buildings for the [[Franklin W. Olin College of Engineering]] in [[Needham, Massachusetts]]. William G. Perry was also hired to transform the [[Endicott Estate]] into a Governor's Mansion.<ref name=elegance/>
